quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  44,1,"Ha Mīm."
  44,2,"By the Evident Scripture,"
  44,3,"We have indeed sent it down on a blessed night{1}. Indeed, We have always been warning.",footnotes:1:This night is known as the night ofQadr (Surah number 97), in the month of Ramadan.
  44,4,"Onit, every wise command is distinguished—"
  44,5,"a command from Us; indeed, We have always been sending"
  44,6,"mercy from your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord—indeed, it is He who is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing—"
  44,7,"<i class=""s"">(from the) </i><span class=""h"">Lord<sup foot_note=""81125"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>of the heavens and the earth and what is between them, if you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a><i class=""s"">(can ever) </i>believe with certitude."
  44,8,"There is no god but He; He gives life and causes death—your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>Lord and the Lord of your ancient fathers."
  44,9,"Yet they play around in doubt."
  44,10,"So wait<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>and watch out for the day when the sky produces evident smoke"
  44,11,"that overwhelms mankind; this is a painful punishment."
  44,12,"“Our Lord, lift the punishment from us; we are truly believers.”"
  44,13,"But how can the reminding benefit them when an evident messenger had already come to them,"
  44,14,"then they turned away from him and said, “<i class=""s"">(He is) </i>taught<i class=""s"">(by others) </i>, a madman!”"
  44,15,"Indeed, if We lift off the punishment a little, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>will revert."
  44,16,"On the day when We assault with the biggest onslaught, We will indeed wreak vengeance upon them."
  44,17,"And surely before them We tested the people of Pharaoh when a noble messenger{1}came to them,",footnotes:1:Prophet Musa, or Moses.
  44,18,"saying, “Hand over Allah’s servants to me; indeed, I am to you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>a trustworthy messenger."
